verbose_text: On the other hand, branched-chain amino acid is reported to increase serum albumin levels in patients with decompensated cirrhosis [XREF_BIBR] and inhibits hepatocarcinogeneis in patients with decompensated cirrhosis with higher baseline body mass index or alpha-fetoprotein levels [XREF_BIBR] and with compensated cirrhosis with lower baseline albumin levels [XREF_BIBR].
